<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="301" type="distribution">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="301">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="301">
United States, Mexico (Baja California, Chiapas, Guanajuato, Jalisco, Morelos, Oaxaca, Puebla, Sonora), Guatemala (
<bibRefCitation author="Young, FN" journalOrPublisher="Quarterly Journal of the Florida Academy of Sciences" pageId="0" pageNumber="301" pagination="56 - 77" publicationUrl="https://www.jstor.org/stable/24314787" refId="B107" refString="Young, FN, 1963. The Nearctic species of Copelatus Erichson (Coleoptera: Dytiscidae). Quarterly Journal of the Florida Academy of Sciences 26: 56 - 77, https://www.jstor.org/stable/24314787" title="The Nearctic species of Copelatus Erichson (Coleoptera: Dytiscidae)." url="https://www.jstor.org/stable/24314787" volume="26" year="1963">Young 1963</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.32870/dugesiana.v6i2.3914" author="Arce-Perez, A" journalOrPublisher="Dugesiana" pageId="0" pageNumber="301" pagination="69 - 104" refId="B6" refString="Arce-Perez, A, Roughley, RE, 1999. Lista anotada y claves para los Hydradephaga (Coleoptera: Adephaga: Dytiscidae, Noteridae, Haliplidae, Gyrinidae) de Mexico. Dugesiana 6 (2): 69 - 104, DOI: https://doi.org/10.32870/dugesiana.v6i2.3914" title="Lista anotada y claves para los Hydradephaga (Coleoptera: Adephaga: Dytiscidae, Noteridae, Haliplidae, Gyrinidae) de Mexico." url="https://doi.org/10.32870/dugesiana.v6i2.3914" volume="6" year="1999">
<normalizedToken originalValue="Arce-Pérez">Arce-Perez</normalizedToken>
and Roughley 1999
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.4580.1.1" author="Zaragoza-Caballero, S" journalOrPublisher="Zootaxa" pageId="0" pageNumber="301" pagination="1 - 122" refId="B108" refString="Zaragoza-Caballero, S, Rodriguez-Miron, GM, Vega-Badillo, V, Gonzalez-Ramirez, M, Zurita-Garcia, M, Dominguez-Leon, ED, Lopez-Perez, S, Gutierrez-Carranza, IG, Cifuentes-Ruiz, P, Perez-Hernandez, CX, Ramirez del Valle, E, Gutierrez, NA, 2019. Checklist of the Coleoptera (Insecta) from Morelos, Mexico. Zootaxa 4580 (1): 1 - 122, DOI: https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.4580.1.1" title="Checklist of the Coleoptera (Insecta) from Morelos, Mexico." url="https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.4580.1.1" volume="4580" year="2019">Zaragoza-Caballero et al. 2019</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Nilsson, AN" journalOrPublisher="Dugesiana" pageId="0" pageNumber="301" publicationUrl="http://www.waterbeetles.eu" refId="B75" refString="Nilsson, AN, Hajek, J, 2020. A World Catalogue of the Family Dytiscidae, or the Diving Beetles (Coleoptera, Adephaga). Version 1.I.2020. National Museum, Prague. http://www.waterbeetles.eu" title="A World Catalogue of the Family Dytiscidae, or the Diving Beetles (Coleoptera, Adephaga). Version 1. I. 2020. National Museum, Prague." url="http://www.waterbeetles.eu" year="2020">
Nilsson and 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Hájek">Hajek</normalizedToken>
2020
</bibRefCitation>
). This species has been recorded from moderate elevations (
<bibRefCitation author="Young, FN" journalOrPublisher="Quarterly Journal of the Florida Academy of Sciences" pageId="0" pageNumber="301" pagination="56 - 77" publicationUrl="https://www.jstor.org/stable/24314787" refId="B107" refString="Young, FN, 1963. The Nearctic species of Copelatus Erichson (Coleoptera: Dytiscidae). Quarterly Journal of the Florida Academy of Sciences 26: 56 - 77, https://www.jstor.org/stable/24314787" title="The Nearctic species of Copelatus Erichson (Coleoptera: Dytiscidae)." url="https://www.jstor.org/stable/24314787" volume="26" year="1963">Young 1963</bibRefCitation>
) and 1,706 m (
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.1007/978-94-017-9109-0_3" author="Miller, KB" editor="Yee, DA" journalOrPublisher="Springer, New York" pageId="0" pageNumber="301" pagination="49 - 172" refId="B63" refString="Miller, KB, Bergsten, J, 2014. The phylogeny and classification of predaceous diving beetles (Coleoptera: Dytiscidae). In: Yee, DA, Ed., Ecology, Systematics, and the Natural History of Predaceous Diving Beetles (Coleoptera: Dytiscidae). Springer, New York: 49 - 172, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1007/978-94-017-9109-0_3" title="The phylogeny and classification of predaceous diving beetles (Coleoptera: Dytiscidae)." url="https://doi.org/10.1007/978-94-017-9109-0_3" volumeTitle="Ecology, Systematics, and the Natural History of Predaceous Diving Beetles (Coleoptera: Dytiscidae)." year="2014">Miller and Bergsten 2014</bibRefCitation>
), herein it was found at levels 3 (1,126-1,194 m), 4 (1,448-1,619 m), and 5 (1,126-1,776 m).
</paragraph>
